comments: Towns (MIN) establishes himself in a screening position in McConnell's (IND) path and does not deliver contact.

Towns (MIN) makes contact to the ball and makes incidental arm contact with Sabonis (IND) as he follows through. Additionally, Towns places a resting hand on Sabonis' back while defending the post play.
Sabonis (IND) and Towns (MIN) both engage for the loose ball ball and get tangled up. A jump ball is correctly whistled.
The play is correctly blown dead to repeat the jump ball toss.
Towns (MIN) establishes himself in a screening position in Holiday's (IND) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Towns (MIN) makes incidental contact with Brogdon's (IND) body after the release of his shot attempt at the basket.
Towns (MIN) establishes himself in Brogdon's (IND) path and gives him a step to avoid contact.
Brogdon (IND) brushes Towns' (MIN) arm during his shot attempt at the basket.
Holiday (IND) and McDaniels (MIN) engage and disengage with one another off ball.
Beasley (MIN) moves slightly lateral in Brogdon's (IND) path and marginal contact occurs during his drive.
Sabonis (IND) briefly places his hand to Rubio's (MIN) front after his gather, and quickly removes it while contesting his driving shot attempt.
Edwards (MIN) moves alongside of Holiday (IND) and makes marginal contact while defending the drive to the basket and the pass.
McDaniels (MIN) makes contact with Sabonis' (IND) head and contact affects his shot attempt at the basket.
Turner (IND) makes marginal contact to Edwards' (MIN) body after the release of his jump shot attempt.
Beasley (MIN) briefly places his hands against Holiday's (IND) body off ball and quickly disengages.
McDaniels (MIN) wraps Sabonis' (IND) during the pick and the contact affects his FOM.

After the pass is received, Beasley (MIN) brushes against Holiday's (IND) face.   Contact to an opponent?s head/face can be deemed marginal when the result of a natural basketball move, provided the contact is not disproportionate or uncontrolled.
Sabonis (IND) establishes himself in a screening position in McDaniels' (MIN) path and absorbs the contact.
Towns (MIN) jumps alongside of Holiday's (IND) path to the basket and marginal contact occurs.
While rolling to the basket, McDaniels (MIN) and Sabonis (IND) engage and disengage in marginal arm to arm contact with one another.
Rubio (MIN) makes marginal contact to Sabonis' (IND) body in the post and he is able to move through the contact.
Lamb (IND) releases the shot attempt prior to the expiration of the shot clock.
Brogdon (IND) moves laterally in Rubio's (MIN) path during his drive and contact affects his SQBR.
Sabonis (IND) cleanly dislodges the pass attempt before incidental contact occurs with Beasley (MIN).
Sabonis (IND) moves in a natural path and makes incidental contact with Beasley (MIN) after the pick.

Lamb (IND) closes out on Beasley (MIN) during his jump shot attempt, but is still moving forward slightly while Beasley is in the air, which makes him illegal even if Beasley?s forward momentum creates the contact.
There is a dual whistle on this play and the foul reported to the table is on Rubio (MIN).  Rubio (MIN) swipes down and makes clean contact with the ball.
